 fitness volunteering primetime fair articles classes and activities wellness fairs career development transitions and return to work balancing one's work demands with family and personal needs can be very challenging the worklife office participates in professional organizations that address these issues and can provide resources to help during times of struggle or change also changing careers or returning to work after having a child or other reason can present new challenges and require extra support worklife staff are available for one on one appointments to help you problem solve these challenges schedule appointment career development centerfor students career development for staff stanford new hires learning and development gateways for students faculty staff post docs hospital staff hr managers others financial programs for employees centers stanford madera grove children's center application stanford arboretum children's center application cclc stanford west application children's center of the stanford community application rainbow school application peppertree after school program application bing nursery school stanford university worklife office 320 panama street bambi modular stanford california 94305 4160 650 723 2660 worklife office is a division of stanford human resources terms of use copyright complaints
